This technique uses the phase difference between the inverter output voltage and the inverter output current to detect islanding [22]. Under normal condition, the voltage and current are synchronized with each other through phase lock loop (PLL). In absence of main grid support, the voltage phase angle will have a sudden jump due to load phase angle creating a huge difference between voltage and current phase angle. If the difference crosses the specified limit, islanding is detected [17, 23]. The equation of the phase-jump algorithm is as in (14).14arctan[(ÎQ/PDG)/(1+ÎP/PDG)]â¤Î±\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
